    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in the Soviet Union (
                        Harriman
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d273</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">273</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-02-24T05:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-02-24T05:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-24T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.61112A/2–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-24T13:00:00+03:00">February 24, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>538. ReEmbs 338, February 6, 1 p.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d273fn22">Not
                        printed.</note> Head of American Section of Foreign Office<note n="23" xml:id="d273fn23">Semen Konstantinovich Tsarapkin.</note> has now replied to
                        Kennan’s<note n="24" xml:id="d273fn24">George F. Kennan, Counselor of
                        American Embassy.</note> letters of November 25 and January 5 concerning
                    recognition of the Proclaimed List and has named an official, the head of Trade
                    Agreements Section of People’s Commissariat for Foreign Trade,<note n="25" xml:id="d273fn25">Pavel Nikolayevich Kumykin.</note> who would be prepared
                    to discuss with us the question of recognition of Proclaimed List by the Soviet
                    Government in its official dealings.</p>
                <p>We will proceed with these discussions as soon as possible.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department as 538; repeated to London as 74.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
